<h2>About us</h2><br>
<p>Kiriri Women's University of Science and Technology, often referred to as KWUST,
     is a non-state funded secular women's university in Nairobi, Kenya.
      It was started in 2002.[1] Its aim is to empower women in sciences.
       Kiriri Women's University is the only women's university in east and southern Africa.
        Its main campus is located in Mwihoko, Githurai in the outskirt of Nairobi. Kiriri has no male students. It offers B.Science degrees in mathematics (actuarial, pure, statistics), computer science and business administration, as well as diplomas and certificates.</p>
